<title>USA: Symmetricom explores spin-off, sale.</title>
<headline>Symmetricom explores spin-off, sale.</headline>
<dateline>SAN JOSE, Calif. 1997-07-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>SymmetriCom Inc Wednesday said it is considering various ways to boost shareholder value including spinning off one or both of its operating units or selling the company outright.</p>
<p>In a statement, SymmetriCom said it intends to hire an investment banking firm for advice. It also could merge with another company or form strategic alliances or joint ventures.</p>
<p>SymmetriCom has two operating units, Telecom Solutions, a global supplier of advanced network synchronization systems for telephone companies, and Linfinity Microelectronics Inc, a maker of linear and mixed signal integrated circuits.</p>
